<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="342" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,402,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="342">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been found only once in 
<collectingCountry box="[777,838,547,573]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="342">India</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Visvesvara, G." box="[847,1050,547,574]" pageId="10" pageNumber="342" pagination="435 - 443" refId="ref14201" refString="Visvesvara, G. (1963) On some Gastrotricha from India with description of two new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6, 435 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936308651379" type="journal article" year="1963">Visvesvara (1963)</bibRefCitation>
reported that the Indian specimens are morphologically similar to the American specimens except for their size (total length 90-114 μm vs 70 μm). The furcal appendages (14-18 μm vs 11 μm), and the pharynx (36-42 μm vs 20 μm) are also reported longer. In consideration of these discrepancies, we regard the presence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1025,1083,655,681]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="342">India</collectingCountry>
to be provisional (i.e., not fully proven).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
